fr.reflexe.viewshell.api.design

Interface IThemedPage

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    IDashboardPage, IDataPage, IFormPage, IListPage, IPasswordAuthnPage

    public interface IThemedPage
    Base interface for pages designed using a template and style sheets.
    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    REFLEXE Technologies
    See Also:
    IThemedDesign

    • Field Detail

      • KEY_CONTEXT_URI

        static final String KEY_CONTEXT_URI
        The template data context key that should be used to pass a reference to the server's base path, when merging template data into a template file.

        This base URI is relative to the embedded HTTP server's endpoint. It starts and ends with "/".

        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • KEY_CONTENT_TYPE

        static final String KEY_CONTENT_TYPE
        The template data context key that should be used to pass a reference to the Content-Type of themed pages.

        When defined, starts with an IETF media type (such as text/html) and may end (depending on type) with a charset suffix.

        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • KEY_PAGE

        static final String KEY_PAGE
        The template data context key that should be used to pass a reference to the current page, when merging template data into a template file. This will be an implementation of IThemedPage (or a subinterface thereof).
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        push(ITemplateData, IHttpServiceCall), Constant Field Values

      • KEY_ASSET

        static final String KEY_ASSET
        The template data context key that should be used to pass the list of assets to apply to the current page, when merging template data into a template file. This will be a list of type IPageAsset.
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        push(ITemplateData, IHttpServiceCall), getAssets(), Constant Field Values

      • KEY_STYLESHEET

        static final String KEY_STYLESHEET
        The template data context key that should be used to pass the list of stylesheets to apply to the current page, when merging template data into a template file. This will be a list of type IStyleSheet.
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        push(ITemplateData, IHttpServiceCall), getStyleSheets(), Constant Field Values

      • KEY_DICTIONARY

        static final String KEY_DICTIONARY
        The template data context key that should be used to pass the list of dictionaries to apply to the current page, when merging template data into a template file. This will be a list of type ITemplateDictionary.
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        push(ITemplateData, IHttpServiceCall), getDictionaries(), ILocaleService.toTemplateDictionary(fr.reflexe.viewshell.api.locale.IDictionary, java.util.Locale), Constant Field Values

    • Method Detail

      • push

        void push(ITemplateData data,
          IHttpServiceCall call)
        Pushes all design elements of the page into a template data context, in the context of an HTTP call.

        This includes at least:

        • page
        • asset
        • styleSheet
        • dictionary
        Parameters:
        data - the non-null template data context for the page, into which references to design elements should be pushed.
        call - the non-null HTTP, for additional context.
        Since:
        1.0

      • getTemplate

        ITemplateFile getTemplate()
        Gets the current template for this page.
        Returns:
        the template, or null if the configured template is not currently available via the OSGi service registry, via the registered IThemeService. If the template is configured with a version range constraint, then the registered instance must also match that constraint.
        Since:
        1.0

      • getStyleSheets

        List<IStyleSheet> getStyleSheets()
        Gets the list of stylesheets for this page. These should be compatible with the current template.
        Returns:
        the list of stylesheets, possibly empty, never null. The list will contain only those instances that are currently available via the OSGi service registry, via the registered IThemeService. If stylesheets are configured with version range constraints, then registered instances must also match these constraints.
        Since:
        1.0

      • getStyleMedia

        String getStyleMedia(IStyleSheet styleSheet)
        Gets the optional media attribute associated with the specified stylesheet for this page, if defined.
        Parameters:
        styleSheet - one of the stylesheets returned by invoked the getStyleSheets() method on this design instance.
        Returns:
        the non-empty value of the media attribute (if defined) or null. With CSS2 (or more recent), this should be either a media query or a media type.
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        StyleMediaType, StyleMediaFeature

      • getAssets

        List<IPageAsset> getAssets()
        Gets the list of assets for this page. These should be compatible with the current template.
        Returns:
        the list of assets, possibly empty, never null. The list will contain only those instances that are currently available via the OSGi service registry. If assets are configured with version range constraints, then registered instances must also match these constraints.
        Since:
        1.0

      • getDictionaries

        List<IDictionary> getDictionaries()
        Gets the list of dictionaries for this page. These should be compatible with the current template.
        Returns:
        the list of dictionaries, possibly empty, never null. The list will contain only those instances that are currently available via the OSGi service registry. If dictionaries are configured with version range constraints, then registered instances must also match these constraints.
        Since:
        1.0
